I've created the Trait Id developer guide at `generated/trait-id.md`. The document covers:

- **Allocating Trait IDs**: How to use `TraitId::Alloc()` to obtain unique identifiers with thread-safety guarantees
- **Comparing Trait IDs**: Using `operator==` and `operator!=` for equality checks, and accessing the `value` member
- **Using Trait IDs with Traits**: How `TraitId` is passed to lifecycle callbacks like `OnAttached` and `OnDetached`

All API references have been verified against the source headers:
- `Dali::Ui::TraitId::Alloc()` - static method returning `TraitId` (trait-id.h, trait-id.cpp)
- `Dali::Ui::TraitId::operator==` and `operator!=` - comparison operators (trait-id.h)
- `Dali::Ui::TraitId::value` - `uint32_t` public member (trait-id.h)
- `Dali::Ui::Integration::TraitImpl` lifecycle callbacks with `TraitId` parameter (trait-impl.h)
- `Dali::Ui::Integration::ReservedTraitId` namespace with framework-reserved IDs (reserved-trait-id.h)
